se'>Keep LetsVPN running in the background (for Huawei users)</span><svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' class='h-5 w-5 text-gray-400' viewBox='0 0 20 20' fill='currentColor'><path fill-rule='evenodd' d='M7.293 14.707a1 1 0 010-1.414L10.586 10 7.293 6.707a1 1 0 011.414-1.414l4 4a1 1 0 010 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0z' clip-rule='evenodd' /></svg></a></li></ul></div><div class='mt-10 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200 text-center'><p class='text-gray-600 mb-4'>Did this answer your question?</p><div class='flex justify-center space-x-4 mt-2'><button class='text-4xl p-2 rounded-full hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors' aria-label='Dissatisfied'>üòû</button><button class='text-4xl p-2 rounded-full hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors' aria-label='Neutral'>üòê</button><button class='text-4xl p-2 rounded-full hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors' aria-label='Satisfied'>üòÉ</button></div></div>"
